ce a weekly position.\nEach position need several sources files to be computed.  TO build the week 23   W23  position we need\nthe F20..F22 sources files :     graph   TD  ;       F20   -->   W23  ;       F21   -->   W23  ;       F22   -->   W23  ;  The sources files may be :   excel file  parquet file  csv file  XBRL file  ...  Explaining the weekly changes :     graph   TD  ;       W22   -->   DW23_22  ;       W23   -->   DW23_22  ;  Overall process :     graph   TD  ;       F10   -->   W22  ;       F11   -->   W22  ;       F12   -->   W22  ;       F20   -->   W23  ;       F21   -->   W23  ;       F22   -->   W23  ;       W22   -->   DW23_22  ;       W23   -->   DW23_22  ;  TODO   a simple pytest test suite to analyse one dataset  a simple python program that compare 2 datasets and generat a report  html.dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark) !important;background: var(--shiki-dark-bg) !important;font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style) !important;font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight) !important;text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration) !important;}"},{"id":"content:_weeklypos:index.md","path":"/_weeklypos","dir":"","title":"WeeklyPos use cases","description":"Progressive use cases on producing a weekly position.\nThe context is very simplified.\nSome detailed scenario :","keywords":["Dummy build report","Dummy check report","Simple check report","Simple build report","Custom report","Delta pos","Check delta pos","Link previous pos","external sources","forge"],"body":"  WeeklyPos use cases  Progressive use cases on producing a weekly position.\n  The context  is very simplified.\nSome detailed scenario :    scenario 1  : Checking a weekly position   scenario 2  : Checking tampered weekly positions   scenario 3  : Producing a weekly position  Progressive cases :  Dummy build report  Simply drop the files you want to seal :   Sources files  include a PRQL file with sensible queries  Computed position as an Excel file  Digitaly sign the resulting PDF and you get /   A digitaly signed PDF (PADES)  Default template including the details  Only details about dropped files (duckdb, excel, ...)  The source files are :   phys.duckdb : Commodity deals  market.duckdb : Market prices  ref.xlsx : Reference entities  futures.csv : Future deals  pos.xlsx : Position summary  Dummy check report  We can only check the signature\nand the precense of mandatory files.  Show some PDF :    weeklypos_2022S44b.pdf  OK: a PDF where everything is OK  KO: identity usurpation (external fraud), use of a weak signature provider   weeklypos_2022S44a.pdf  KO: missing file (internal error/fraud)  KO: incorrect file (Excel file must containes a named range 'POS_TOTAL' and 'POS_DATE')  KO: data mismatch signature/position (internal error/fraud)  Simple check report  The Python script that build the position\nis also able to check the position.  Create a checklist that will use this script to chek any existing position.  The script will fail if something is wrong with the pos.   This is where   PuffinDB  will shine as the check process will be much faster.  Show some PDF :    weeklypos_2022S44b.pdf  OK: a PDF where everything is OK   weeklypos_2022S44a.pdf  KO: some source data values does not match and the signature is KO (external fraud)   weeklypos_2022S44c.pdf  KO: some source data values does not match but the signature is OK (internal error/fraud)  Simple build report  We may also use the Python build script to enterily generate the position. The user has only to provide the source files.   This is where   PuffinDB  will shine as the build process will be much faster.  Custom report  An Office template for a custom report.\nThe report includes some values from the Excel file and SQL queries result (values and table).  Add some instructions in the templates to check or rerun the position.  Show how you can drop a new template.  Delta pos  Delta: Compare/explain 2 positions   for weekly/monthly/quarter/yearly delta  for same week data fix  Show a craft form where you drop 2 pos\nand you build the resulting comparaison PDF.  Check delta pos  Checklist that show the detailed delta :   What's new  What's changed  What's deleted  Link previous pos  Change the build position craft form to include a delta.\nlet the user drop a PDF of the previsou position.\nCompute/include the defailed delta in the new position.   This is where   PuffinDB  will shine as the build process will be much faster.  external sources  You can link/query external sources.   This is where   PuffinDB  will shine as the build process will be much faster.   We are working on a feature that could check if the exernal data source has changed (by computing/comparing a hash).  forge  This entire story has been produced with our forge.\nThe forge includes everything you need to create and check PDF.\nSome of the forge features are :   produce fake PDF documents  produce deep nested PDF documents  digitally sign PDF documents  automate the PDF documents production  test/debug your custom check module  S3 storage for all your documents  based on Jupyter notebook  TODO   get real sample data (or generate some)  a simple pytest test suite to analyse one dataset  a simple python program that compare 2 datasets and generat a report  API case to show how to build a PDsF  API case to show how to check several PDF (a chain of positions in a big audit)  add a blockchain hash check (for a quarter position only)  add a XBRL source file  external source : live market data  create a temp VM on a PDF drop to restore the whole data env"},{"id":"content:_weeklypos:scenario1.md","path":"/_weeklypos/scenario1","dir":"_weeklypos","title":"weeklypos scenario 1","description":"","keywords":[],"body":"  weeklypos scenario 1   Check a weekly position by dropping  single PDF  See that everything is OK  Launch a notebook with all the attached data source files "},{"id":"content:_weeklypos:scenario2.md","path":"/_weeklypos/scenario2","dir":"_weeklypos","title":"weeklypos scenario 2","description":"","keywords":[],"body":"  weeklypos scenario 2   Check a weekly position by dropping  single PDF  See that it fails (KO)  Get the reason : wrong signature (usurpation)  Another failing PDF : broken signature (data file modified)  Another failing PDF : missing file  Another failing PDF : different result  Another failing PDF : incoherent result  Eventualy get the good PDF where everything is OK"},{"id":"content:_weeklypos:scenario3.md","path":"/_weeklypos/scenario3","dir":"_weeklypos","title":"weeklypos scenario 3","description":"Build a weekly pos :","keywords":[],"body":"  weeklypos scenario 3  Build a weekly pos :   drop data sources files  drop previous PDF  see the computed position  generate the final PDF  sign it  check the generated signed PDF -> OK"},{"id":"content:0.index.md","path":"/","dir":"","title":"Home","description":"","keywords":[],"body":"          "},{"id":"content:05.solutions:10.check_user.md","path":"/solutions/check_user","dir":"solutions","title":"check user","description":"check user point of view","keywords":[],"body":"  check user point of view  Drop a PDF document ...\n... go to a   specialized portal .  those   augmented PDF are crafted"},{"id":"content:05.solutions:50.compliance.md","path":"/solutions/compliance","dir":"solutions","title":"compliance","description":"","keywords":[],"body":""},{"id":"content:05.solutions:50.craft_user.md","path":"/solutions/craft_user","dir":"solutions","title":"craft user","description":"to craft a new document a wizard is presented ...","keywords":[],"body":"  to craft a new document a wizard is presented ...  crafted documents are   checked   craft devops   craft investor   craft publisher"},{"id":"content:05.solutions:50.opensource_user.md","path":"/solutions/opensource_user","dir":"solutions","title":"open source","description":"we rely on standards","keywords":[],"body":"  we rely on standards  PDF,  economic figures of open source  opensource is the   only way to go